  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\nSee https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/pull/273#discussion_r161866203\r\nIn `ExecutionContext` (evm.vm.execution_context) and `TransactionContext` (#327), it's better to write an explicit decorator `read_only_property` or `immutable_property` which includes a setter that raises such an `AttributeError` when someone try to modify these properties.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n1. Write the decorator in [eth-utils](https://github.com/ethereum/eth-utils) or a new file `evm/utils/decorators.py`\r\n2. Update the decorator of `ExecutionContext` and `TransactionContext`\r\n",
